headline: UPS RFID Rollout Puts Automation And Service Quality In Investor Focus
summary: United Parcel Service (NYSE:UPS) is rolling out RFID package tracking across all 5,500 The UPS Store locations. The move expands UPS's "Smart Package Smart Facility" program, aiming to improve shipment visibility and reduce handling errors. RFID labels are expected to support more precise tracking for both individual and commercial customers using The UPS Store network. UPS, trading at $116.74, is adding this RFID rollout on top of a mixed multi year return profile, with shares up 12.6%...

headline: January Sees Surge in Layoff Plans, Outplacement Firm Says
summary: U.S. job-cut announcements surged in January, according to outplacement firm Challenger, Gray & Christmas.  The firm counted 108,435 announced job cuts last month.   That was up sharply from the roughly 35,500 job cuts announced in December and 49,800 in January 2025.

headline: US applications for jobless benefits jump by 22,000 to 231,000 last week, the most in 2 months.
summary: The number of Americans applying for unemployment benefits jumped last week but remains in the same historically low range of the past few years.  Applications for jobless aid for the week ending Jan. 31 rose by 22,000 to 231,000 from the previous week, the Labor Department reported Thursday.  Applications for unemployment benefits are seen as representative of U.S. layoffs and are close to a real-time indicator of the health of the job market.

headline: Longstanding AIM Mail Center Franchisee Renews Commitment to Serving Lake Wylie, South Carolina and Names Daughter as Co-Owner
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is proud to announce the renewal of a franchise agreement for the AIM Mail Center location in Lake Wylie, South Carolina. This renewal reflects the ongoing dedication of Richard Winter with the addition of his daughter, Ashli Ornoski, to the business. Now that she is incorporated into the family business, they can continue providing essential shipping and office services to the local community.
